: 1039, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"an image problem\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, it represents one of the most beautiful cities on the planet, and yes, it is the face of the Games to the world, but it also represents \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 water so polluted that swimming was banned in it for the lastcentury.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most beautiful cities\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1151}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 water\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"the lastcentury\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, Paris Olympic organizers decided to invest $1.5 billion in cleaning up the river\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and its image.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.364130135866207e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the river\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"its image\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1415}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They promised to make the Seine safe enough for Olympic triathletes and open-water swimmers to compete in.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.568394541193505e-38, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic triathletes\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"open-water swimmers\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(On Monday, officialscancelled the swim portion of triathlon trainingfor a second straight day due to concerns about the water quality.)\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"the swim portion\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"triathlon\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"the water quality\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Short of swimming its length\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll leave that to Olympic athletes and mayors\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094maybe the best way to tell the story of this all-important waterway is, ironically, towalkit.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its length\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"mayors\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094maybe the best way\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1766}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"this all-important waterway\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I start my Day Along the Seine at sunrise in Montmartre.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1888, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.488725872627415e-37, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my Day\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"sunrise\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In my mind are the words of Roman philosopher Marcus Aurelius, who loved river metaphors as much as Noah Lyles lovesYu-Gi-Oh!cards: Meditate often on the swiftness with which all that exists and is coming into being is swept by us and carried away.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 2149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1928, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999970652013281, \"rank\": 2.9318471446258514e-06, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.021694384179268e-20, \"text\": \"Marcus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\"}, {\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my mind\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"river metaphors\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the swiftness\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For substance is like a river\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s unending flow, its activities continually changing and causes infinitely shifting so that almost nothing at all stands still.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"substance\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"a river\